          <avActivityHighlights>At elevated altitudes a considerable avalanche danger will prevail.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>In the regions exposed to heavier precipitation the avalanche prone locations will become more prevalent. &lt;br/&gt; The avalanche-prone wind slabs must be evaluated with care and prudence. The avalanche prone locations are to be found adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls, and behind abrupt changes in the terrain. Moist avalanches are possible as a consequence of the precipitation. Avalanches can penetrate down to the ground. They can be released by a single winter sport participant.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>The fresh and older wind slabs are lying on top of a weakly bonded old snowpack. Weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on shady slopes. The weather conditions will give rise to increasing moistening of the snowpack in particular at low and intermediate altitudes.</snowpackStructureComment>
          <tendencyComment>The weather will be mostly sunny.</tendencyComment>
